=begin pod
=head2 clear-slist

Clears a pointer to a GSList, freeing it and, optionally, freeing its elements using C<$destroy>.
 C<$slist_ptr> must be a valid pointer. If C<$slist_ptr> points to a null GSList, this does nothing.

=begin code
method clear-slist ( N-SList() $slist-ptr, &destroy )
=end code

=item $slist-ptr; a GSList return location.
=item &destroy; the function to pass to C<.free-full()> or C<Nil> to not free elements. Tthe function must be specified with following signature; C<:( gpointer $data )>.

=end pod

